data: Jack Curry (Peter Frechette), a gay man with AIDS, is accused of murdering another gay man with AIDS and claims it was a mercy killing. NBC reportedly lost $1 million in revenue when advertisers pulled out of this and another 1990 episode.
Dan is upset that DJ wants to be a witch for Halloween, while Roseanne dresses up as a man.
Blanche and Dorothy are mistaken for a couple on a talk show.
A politician opposes the prosecution of his son's murderer because it might mean revealing that his late son was gay.
"Come Out, Come Out, Wherever You Are"
The investigation into a ten year-old death reveals that a husband murdered his wife after discovering she was in love with another woman.
George learns that his ex-girlfriend is now dating a woman and he blames himself for turning her into a lesbian.
Mickey and Roger break up and Mickey moves in with Martin. Martin admits he is uncomfortable with his father's sexuality but the two come to an understanding.
Carter helps a suicidal transgender patient.
[The_One_with_the_Sonogram_at_the_End|The One with the Sonogram at the End]
One of the stories involves an innocent man who is afraid to tell the police that he is gay and was with his boyfriend at the time of the crime.
"More Than Friends: The Coming Out of Heidi Leiter"
Based on the true story of Heidi Leiter, who attended her senior prom in Virginia with her girlfriend.
A gay man is a part of a seminar lecture on how to stop being too dependent on men.
The "Ducky Lucky Pre-School" representative mistakes Miles as gay and assures him that the pre-school welcomes same-sex parents.
Ron and Erick have a commitment ceremony.
A priest's body is located in a park used by male prostitutes.
Russell Emerson returns for a second visit and announces that he and his husband are relocating to Paris because of America's racism and homophobia.
Kelly learns that Alison has feelings for her.
The episode's two immortal villains are cryptically depicted as a gay couple.
Neo-Nazis kill a man because he is gay, in a gay neighborhood.
An openly gay city councilman is murdered by a bigoted rival politician.
The detectives investigate the murder of a gay bar owner.
An alien takes control of the body of an engaged and chaste college student, causing her to engage in causal sex, prostitution and lesbian sex.
Leonard (Steve Paymer) expresses in an interest in the "girl" at the impound lot.
A devastated Annie, forced by a medical condition to stop hormone treatments, commits suicide.
A lawyer is fired for being gay and then killed to prevent his sex discrimination lawsuit from outing another lawyer.
The girls patronize a gay bar.
A mercy killer is poisoning patients at an AIDS clinic supposedly to spare them the suffering that her daughter went through.
Jarod Pretends to be a lawyer in California to defend a mentally-challenged man on death row, enlisting the aid of a transvestite cab driver along the way.
Bev embarks on a journey with Scott and Leon to find out the truth about her father.
Chuck Fishman poses as Gary's boyfriend, to help Gary escape from sequestered jury duty in order to prevent an innocent man from being convicted.
Grace and her business partner find out that their investor is gay.
A television commercial for the bar accidentally attracts lots of gay patrons.
A drag queen seeks the squad's protection from her boyfriend.
A deadly bisexual love triangle is featured.
A woman pretends to be a lesbian so she can seduce and murder her stepmother to prevent her from inheriting her father's money. She acknowledges enjoying the seduction more than she expected.

data: The floor of the trunk was made to resemble the hardwood floor of a professional basketball court. WCC painted the car with a custom bright green in the front that faded into a dark green from the midpoint towards the rear of the car.
The owner drove the car only on weekends and kept it on cinder-blocks to prevent theft. Three days after this episode aired, the owner's grandmother died of gastric cancer.
Since the owner liked to go camping, a Tonneau cover was placed over the rear box and was made to lift up vertically. Once opened, the tonneau became a camping tent.
This was the first car to visually get a brand-new engine, as the old engine died before Xzibit could pull it into the shop.

data: "It's a Good Day For Meeting the President's Daughter"
"Guess Who's Coming to the White House?"

Adam decides that he needs to buy a spectacular enagement ring for Nancy because she is the daughter of the President, but he finds that he cannot afford any ring that he thinks will be nice enough for her.
"It's a Bad Day For Meeting Presidents"
A computer analyzes Nancy and Adam and determines them to be incompatible.

Wanting to maintain his privacy, Adam rejects a request to appear in a televised press conference to discuss his engagement to Nancy – but after he acquiesces and appears at the press conference, he begins to act like a television star.
"East is East and West is West"
After Adam meets some of Nancy ' s friends, he worries that a small-town veterinarian like him will never fit into her sophisticated world.
Secret Service concerns about Nancy ' s security block the couple ' s plans for a nice honeymoon away from Abby and the Secret Service, so Nancy and Adam sneak away to Lake Bageneehawk.
Adam ' s house is too small to accommodate Nancy, Abby, and the two Secret Service men assigned to Nancy, so Nancy and Adam need to decide whether they should move to a bigger home.
"First One Hundred Years Are the Hardest"

Nancy and Adam move to a new house on a farm, but their first day there is difficult because Nancy has forgotten to have the utilities turned on and the moving company has gone on strike, leaving them with no furniture.
Nancy has too many duties to perform as daughter of the President, so she gives up her role of helping her father in his political career.
Jim Nielson, the most eligible man in Iowa, courts Abby, but she turns down his proposal of marriage.
Wednesday is Adam ' s "Boys' Night Out," and even though Nancy and Adam would rather be together that night, neither will admit it.
"Never Look a Gift Horse in the Mouth"

As a wedding present, Lord and Lady Halford give Nancy and Adam the services of Milton – a very proper English butler – for a year, and Milton becomes a problem for the newlyweds when he keeps getting in their way.

After Nancy spends too much money decorating Adam ' s office, she discusses the couple ' s financial problems with her father the President, resulting in a number of government agencies attempting to help Nancy and Adam with their finances and the couple almost losing their farm.

Nancy and Adam take in a stray dog with a hand-painted star on his neck and name him Star. Star knows a number of impressive tricks, leading Adam to think he might be a performing dog. Soon the New Jersey Continental Circus contacts Adam to inform him that Star belongs to them and they want him back. Nancy adores Star, so to avoid hurting her feelings, Adam schemes to return Star to his rightful owners and replace him with a lookalike dog on which he has painted a star in the hope that Nancy will not notice the difference.

The sisters then cast a spell to track down the banshee which turns Prue into a dog, but when Prue gets hit by a car, the driver takes her home to care for her, thus taking her out of the action. When the banshee attacks the Halliwell manor she surprised Phoebe in the attic and, sensing her immense pain (what the banshee feeds on) over Cole's betrayal, screams at her. It is later discovered that although this scream would kill mortals, it has a very different effect on witches: it turns them into a banshee too. Piper blows the Banshee up but it is too late, Phoebe has already turned into a banshee. Leo warns Piper that if Phoebe kills, she will stay a banshee forever.

At the beginning of the episode, Prue and Piper bring a doctor to the manor, to protect him from a powerful demonic assassin named Shax, who was sent by The Source. When Shax breaks into the manor, he throws Prue and Piper through a wall, causing them to almost die, until Leo arrives with enough time to heal them. Phoebe uses a vanquishing spell on Shax but it does not kill him. While searching for Shax out in the streets, Prue and Piper are caught on live television using their powers, thus exposing themselves as witches. As a crowd forms around their house, a mentally unstable girl, claiming to want to join The Charmed Ones' coven, breaks in, only to be thrown out by Prue. Phoebe goes to the Underworld to find Cole and whilst there they are there, they are forced to strike a deal with Tempus to travel back in time to before it was revealed that magic existed. They travel back successfully but the episode ends with Phoebe, Cole and Leo trapped in the Underworld and Prue and Piper lying unconscious on the floor from when Shax blasted them in his initial attack, neither of them moving, one or both of them possibly dead.
